subSubSection.paragraph:
Grammostola chalcothrix

can be recognized by the following combination of characters: presence of long spiniform setae on prolateral and retrolateral coxal aspects of legs I–III, prolateral coxae IV and retrolateral palpal maxillae; male palpal bulb pyriform with PI developed and PS well developed, slightly curved and very long embolus (
Figure 4A, B
); two long and curved spermathecal receptacles (
Schiapelli and Gerschman 1961
).
